    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chisel-like tools designed for use in plumbing, typically having a blunt end and curved blades, pushed ans struck with a hammer to force lead and oakum in the collars of pipes to make them watertight.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
